<br>
Wizards a very clear class to judge other classes on casting damage.<br>
<br>
Direct damage:<br>
   Wiz &gt; mag &gt; nec/enc<br>
<br>
Dot:<br>
   Nec &gt; enc &gt; mag/wiz<br>
<br>
Indirect damage (pets):<br>
   mag &gt; enc/nec &gt; wiz<br>
<br>
Non damage abilities (buffs, ports etc):<br>
   Enc &gt; mag/nec/wiz <br>
<br>
Priest classes:<br>
<br>
dots:<br>
  Shm &gt; druid &gt; cleric<br>
<br>
Nukes (not sure on this one):<br>
  Druid &gt; cleric &gt; shm<br>
<br>
Healing:<br>
  Cleric &gt; druid/shm<br>
<br>
Utility (ports, buffs, etc):<br>
  Druid &gt; shm &gt; cleric<br>
<br>
I suppose warriors would be the next benchmark.  As you increase in damage above the warrior, you should lose proportional tanking ability.  As you lose damage in relation to the warrior, you should gain in abilites such as spells/songs.  Tanking ability should also go down when gaining spells etc.<br>
<br>
So on the melee scale:<br>
<br>
Damage:<br>
   Rog &gt; monk &gt; war &gt; rang/shd/pal/beast &gt; bard<br>
   Looks fair, right now i don't care to distinguish the hybrids atm.<br>
<br>
Tanking ability:<br>
   War &gt; monk/rang/shd/pal/beast/rog &gt; bard<br>
   No particular order for hybrids and monk, but gives a sort of idea about where it should be.<br>
<br>
Abilities/spells<br>
<br>
Bard/pal/shd/rang/beast &gt; rog/monk &gt; war<br>
<br>
Everything has has a slash, is too close to call whether one is better than the other in my opinion.<br>
