Each class is different and has its advatages and disadvantages. Each class has a niche. If you picked a warrior you did it to be a bad arse tank and be THE man in the high end encounter. If you picked a monk it was to deal good damage and still take some as well and to pull for your group. (this is a broad example)<br>
I play a 60 monk. I would never tank over a 60 warrior in an exp group. The difference in how often the cleric has to heal when I tank is ... the cleric can not melee with me tanking. where as when my warrior friend tanks the cleric can melee and we can plow threw many more mobs and get more exp.<br>
Any melee class can tank its just about who does it best.Warriors Tank the best period. Can a monk tank? sure can a ranger tank? sure. even a rogue could tank, its all about the support you get from your group. The whole point is risk vs reward on the gear like you all are talking about the flayed barb legs. 60 ac is very nice. You have to be in a guild and prob be with them for 2 plus years to even get a chance at these. Dont nerf monks or any other class because VI put out some kick arse gear to give peeps something to strive for.<br>
If the proposed nerf takes effect and is bad as everyone assumes, monks will be a lot less desirable class to group with and to play. There is no need for balance unless it effects a majority of the other players/classes. monks dont plain and simple. However nerfing them will. <br>
