<br>
I appreciate your input, but I'd really like to keep the focus of this thread to my original point.  This was spawned by the recent discussions due to the impending changes, but is not a sounding board regarding them.  We have 1000+ other forums where everyone is voicing their opinions about the changes, and I respectfully request those wishing to post about that topic in one of those.<br>
<br>
This thread is not about balancing classes, as VI/SOE will do what they please regarding that.  Instead, it's aobut us as a player-base determining what we place our value upon so we can perform our own calculations and see where we feel that state of balance is.  We cannot come to VI/SOE with broad generalized statements like &quot;we need to better balanced&quot;, or &quot;class x is better than class y&quot;.  If we are to accomplish anything, we need to be able to have something solid to compare and agree upon, and &quot;hopefully&quot; be able to accomplish what we need as one big team.<br>
<br>
However, one of the things you stated merits special attention.  You stated that each class has it special nitch.  You are absolutely correct.  They part of that we need to be aware of is that, based upon gear, situation, game changes, expansions, etc... those nitches have been known to change, and will most likely change again.  The information I'm hoping to have put together will allow everyone to better determine what those nitches are, should be, or might become in the future. <p>Raphayl <BR>
